stylometry: @RISK ouptu shows you the following: standard deviation, maximum profits, minimum profits, and the average profit, what you are looking for when making a decision is you are taking all those numbers into consideration to form the outcome that wil lead to your best conclusion. you always want a standard deviation on the the low end, because you want reliable data. your max and min profits ares also to be considered but they have to rely on the standard deviation, if the max is high and SD is high than that is not a good relationship. You wnt to have some distance but not a lot between SD and the max or in some cases min. Then the average profit is something you want on the higher end because you can rely on that information to be consistantly close.
